AECOM has an immediate requirement for a Work Supervisor I to work on a large multi-disciplinary private project in Hong Kong. The project is located at Sai Sha, Shap Sze Heung, Sai Kung. The general nature of the proposed works include widening of Sai Sha Road between Sai O Village and Tai Tung Village from a 2-lane carriageway to a dual 2-lane carriageway; construction of a new carriageway from Tai Tung Village to Tseng Tau Village; construction of three footbridges near Nai Chung, Kwan Hang and Ma Kwu Lam Village; construction of footpaths and cycle tracks; and ancillary works including earthworks, drainage works, sewage and sewerage works, landscaping works, construction of box culverts, retaining walls, reconstruction of existing open space public carpark and public bus terminus and construction of noise barriers;

The works have commenced in 2018 with anticipated completion date in 4th quarter of Year 2024.

The successful applicant would be offered a 24-month contract initially and subject to renewal depending on the project’s ongoing needs.
 
Responsibilities:


Assist in supervising site works carried out by the Contractor;
Take site measurements;
Ensure the site works are constructed in accordance with Contract specifications, drawings and site instructions;
Check material quality and workmanship;
Keep sites records, diary, weather chart, progress report, piling records, material delivery records etc.;
Check that all Contractor's site staff observe safety precautions for the Works to be carried out;
Keep and update site records;
Deal with any other duties as may be assigned from time to time by the superior.
 

Requirements:

Certificate from a Hong Kong Polytechnic/ Polytechnic University, the Hong Kong Institute of Vocational Education or HKSAR technical institute or equivalent in an appropriate discipline or completed a technician apprenticeship; and

At least 3 years relevant post-qualification experience

