AECOM is seeking a Resident Engineer to be based in Hong Kong.
Act as RSE T5 & RSE/RGE T3 and both the RSE/RGE’s Representative full time on site;
Accountable and report to the AP/RSE/RGE and take-in-charge of the RE Site Office for implementing the RSE/RGE’s supervision;
Take overall responsibility to check the site safety measures in compliance with requirements of supervision plans;
Carry out specific tasks as per requirements and checklist devised from RSE/RGE and representative of Client;
Supervise the junior TCPs comprising Assistant Resident Engineers to check the essential items for specified tasks, including but not limited to demolition works;
Coordinate and compile reports on supervision activities including reports on non-conformities, to deal with non-conformities, and to report to RSE/RGE;
Check the works in compliance with the approved plans, the approved temporary works, method statements, precautionary and protective measures;
Review Contractor’s submissions;
Monitor the work of the Registered Contractor’s TCPs;
Attend the site meetings and project meetings, and assist and coordinate with the design office for all site works/matters.
Check the contractor’s structural works are in compliance with the statutory and contractual requirements.
Enforce ethics and compliance policy including Third Party payment, Sub-consultancy engagement process and Gift and Entertainment policy.
